 of the law namely the duty of care owed by a corporations officers and board to its shareholders eisner later revealed in  interview with the hollywood reporter that he regretted letting ovitz go eisner attempted in  to purchase nbc from general electric ge but the deal failed due to ge wanting to keep  percent ownership of the network disney acquired many other media sources during the decade including a merger with capital citiesabc in  which brought broadcast network abc and its assets including the ae television networks and espn networks into the disney fold eisner felt that the purchase of abc was an important investment to keep disney surviving and allowing it to compete with international multimedia conglomerates disney lost a  million lawsuit in september  to marsu bv over disneys failure to produce as contracted  halfhour marsupilami cartoon shows instead disney felt other internal hot properties deserved the companys attention disney which had taken control of the anaheim angels in  purchased a majority stake in the team in  that same year disney began a move into the internet field with the purchase of starwave and  percent of infoseek in  disney purchased the remaining shares of infoseek and launch the go network portal in january disney also launched its cruise line with the christening of disney magic and a sister ship disney wonder the katzenberg case dragged on as his contract included a portion of the film revenue from ancillary markets forever katzenberg had offered  to settle the case but eisner felt the original claim amount of about half a billion too much but then the ancillary market clause was found disney lawyers tried to indicate a decline situation which reveal some of the problems in the company abc had declining rating and increasing costs while the film segment had two film failures while neither party revealed the settlement amount it is estimated at  million eisners controlling style inhibited efficiency and progress according to so