isner and the rest of the disney board because they had not violated the letter of the law namely the duty of care owed by a corporations officers and board to its shareholders eisner later revealed in  interview with the hollywood reporter that he regretted letting ovitz go eisner attempted in  to purchase nbc from general electric ge but the deal failed due to ge wanting to keep  percent ownership of the network disney acquired many other media sources during the decade including a merger with capital citiesabc in  which brought broadcast network abc and its assets including the ae television networks and espn networks into the disney fold eisner felt that the purchase of abc was an important investment to keep disney surviving and allowing it to compete with international multimedia conglomerates disney lost a  million lawsuit in september  to marsu bv over disneys failure to produce as contracted  halfhour marsupilami cartoon shows instead disney felt other internal hot properties deserved the companys attention disney which had taken control of the anaheim angels in  purchased a majority stake in the team in  that same year disney began a move into the internet field with the purchase of starwave and  percent of infoseek in  disney purchased the remaining shares of infoseek and launch the go network portal in january disney also launched its cruise line with the christening of disney magic and a sister ship disney wonder the katzenberg case dragged on as his contract included a portion of the film revenue from ancillary markets forever katzenberg had offered  to settle the case but eisner felt the original claim amount of about half a billion too much but then the ancillary market clause was found disney lawyers tried to indicate a decline situation which reveal some of the problems in the company abc had declining rating and increasing costs while the film segment had two film failures while neither party revealed the settlement amount it is estimated at  million eisners controlling style inhibited efficiency and progress according to some critics while other industry experts indicated that age compression theory led to a decline in the companys target market due to youth copying teenage behavior earlier the year  brought an increase in revenue of  percent and net income of  percent with abc and espn leading the way and parks and resorts marking its sixth consecutive year of growth however the september  attacks led to a decline in vacation travel and the early s recession led to a decrease in abc revenue plus eisner had the company make an expensive purchase of fox family worldwide  was a year of cost cutting laying off  employees disney parks operations decreased slashing annual liveaction film investment and minimizing internet operations while  revenue had a small decrease from  with the cost cutting net income rose to  billion with two creative film releases in  disney became the first studio to record over  billion in worldwide box office receipts eisner did not want the board to renominate roy e disney the son of disney cofounder roy o disney as a board director citing his age of  as a required retirement age stanley gold responded by resigning from the board and requesting the other board members oust eisner in  disney resigned from his positions as the companys vice chairman and chairman of walt disney feature animationchwdc  accusing eisner of micromanagement failures with the abc television network timidity in the theme park business turning the walt disney company into a rapacious soulless company and refusing to establish a clear succession plan as well as a string of boxoffice movie flops starting in the year  on may   disney sold their stake in the anaheim angels baseball team to arte moreno disney purchased the rights to the muppets and the bear in the big blue house franchises from the jim henson company on february   the two brands were placed under control of the muppets holding company llc a unit of disney consumer products in  pixar animation studios began looking for another distributor after its year contract with disney ended due to its strained relationship over issues of control and money with eisner also that year comcast corporation made an unsolicited  billion bid to acquire disney a couple of high budget movies flopped at the box office with these difficulties and with some board directors dissatisfied eisner ceded the board chairmanship on march   at disneys annual shareholders meeting a surprising  of disneys shareholders predominantly rallied by former board members roy disney and stanley gold withheld their proxies to reelect eisner to the board disneys board then gave the chairmanship position to mitchell however the board did not immediately remove eisner as chief executivechwdc  in  disney sold the mighty ducks of anaheim hockey team to henry and susan samueli on march   robert a iger was announced as eisner successor as ceo on september  eisner resigned both as an executive and as a member of the board of directorschwdc  a view of downtown celebration florida the community was planned by the walt disney company –present the bob iger era this section reads like a press release or a news article andor is entirely based on routine coverage please expand this article with properly sourced content to meet wikipedias quality standards event notability guideline andor encyclopedic content policy june  team disney burbank which houses the offices of disneys ceo and several other senior corporate officials on july   walt disneys nephew roy e disney returned to the company as a consultant and as nonvoting director emeritus walt disney parks and resorts celebrated the th anniversary of disneyland park on july  and opened hong kong disneyland on september  walt disney feature animation released chicken little the companys first film using d animation on october  iger replaced eisner as ceo miramax cofounders bob weinstein and harvey weinstein also departed