brands were placed under control of the muppets holding company llc a unit of disney consumer products in  pixar animation studios began looking for another distributor after its year contract with disney ended due to its strained relationship over issues of control and money with eisner also that year comcast corporation made an unsolicited  billion bid to acquire disney a couple of high budget movies flopped at the box office with these difficulties and with some board directors dissatisfied eisner ceded the board chairmanship on march   at disneys annual shareholders meeting a surprising  of disneys shareholders predominantly rallied by former board members roy disney and stanley gold withheld their proxies to reelect eisner to the board disneys board then gave the chairmanship position to mitchell however the board did not immediately remove eisner as chief executivechwdc  in  disney sold the mighty ducks of anaheim hockey team to henry and susan samueli on march   robert a iger was announced as eisner successor as ceo on september  eisner resigned both as an executive and as a member of the board of directorschwdc  a view of downtown celebration florida the community was planned by the walt disney company –present the bob iger era this section reads like a press release or a news article andor is entirely based on routine coverage please expand this article with properly sourced content to meet wikipedias quality standards event notability guideline andor encyclopedic content policy june  team disney burbank which houses the offices of disneys ceo and several other senior corporate officials on july   walt disneys nephew roy e disney returned to the company as a consultant and as nonvoting director emeritus walt disney parks and resorts celebrated the th anniversary of disneyland park on july  and opened hong kong disneyland on september  walt disney feature animation released chicken little the companys first film using d animation on october  iger replaced ei